// src/pages/outdoor/pizza-oven-repair/brands/alfresco.astro
// Wave 7c — Alfresco AXE pizza oven brand page (built-in luxury tier).
// Distinct from /outdoor/brands/alfresco/ (grill product line) — same parent
// (BBQG Inc., Commerce, CA) but separate product family. Cross-link prominent.
// AXE-30 stone hearth gas-fired, $4,000-8,000 unit cost, year 12-18 service
// life. Repair always justified through year 15. $120 outdoor universal.
// BHGS #A49573 + EPA 608 #1346255700410. Em-dash budget ≤2.

import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/outdoor/pizza-oven-repair/brands/alfresco/";

const title = "Alfresco AXE Pizza Oven Repair LA | Built-In Stone Hearth Service | $120";
const description = "Alfresco AXE-30 built-in pizza oven service. BBQG Inc. (Commerce, CA). BH/Calabasas/Hidden Hills outdoor kitchens.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "How is Alfresco's AXE pizza oven different from their grill product line?",
    a: "Same parent company (BBQG Inc., Commerce, CA), different product family. The Alfresco grill line covers built-in gas grills (multiple sizes, search-and-sear and standard burner configurations) and the AXE pizza oven is a separate built-in product family focused on the 30-inch gas-fired stone hearth pizza oven. We service both lines through Alfresco's authorized parts pipeline. Service tickets often combine both because they're typically installed in the same outdoor kitchen build. See our <a href='/outdoor/brands/alfresco/'>Alfresco grill service page</a> for the grill product line."
  },
  {
    q: "Why is Alfresco AXE repair always justified through year 15?",
    a: "Built-in luxury tier math. The AXE-30 is a $4,000 to $8,000 unit installed in a $50,000 to $200,000 outdoor kitchen. The unit is engineered with commercial-grade refractory insulation, heavy-gauge stainless construction, and serviceable component design intended for 15+ year service life. Most failures we see (igniter, gas valve, hearth replacement, refractory rebuild) run $260 to $1,200 in parts. Even at year 14 with a $1,200 repair, the math works because the alternative is $4,000+ unit cost plus cabinet refit. We see Alfresco AXE units from 2015 still running strong."
  },
  {
    q: "My AXE-30 won't reach 700°F anymore. Refractory rebuild or gas valve?",
    a: "We test both at the $120 diagnostic. Symptoms point to either (a) insulation degradation in the dome ceiling — refractory cement cracked from years of thermal cycling, year 8 to 12 typical, or (b) gas valve regulating below spec — manometer test at the burner inlet confirms. Sometimes both at once on year 12+ units. Insulation rebuild $440 to $780 plus refractory materials. Gas valve replacement $260 to $440. If both are needed, $780 to $1,200 total covers the major refresh and the unit goes another 5 to 7 years."
  },
  {
    q: "Does the AXE stone hearth really crack at year 7-12?",
    a: "Yes, but it's not a defect, it's expected wear. The stone hearth absorbs and radiates heat as part of the cooking process. Over years of thermal cycling, hairline surface cracks develop. Through-cracks where the hearth is structurally compromised need replacement; surface cracks are cosmetic. Replacement runs $260 to $560 depending on configuration. We rotate or replace based on actual structural condition, not cosmetic appearance."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you do annual maintenance visits on AXE installations?",
    a: "Yes. Most Beverly Hills, Calabasas, Hidden Hills, and Newport Coast clients run annual or biannual preventive maintenance on full outdoor kitchen suites (grill + pizza oven + outdoor refrigeration). One $120 dispatch covers diagnostic across all components in the suite plus deep cleaning, gas valve manometer check, igniter inspection, refractory inspection. Catches insulation cracks at year 8 before they cost a full rebuild at year 12."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty on every repair. BHGS #A49573 and EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410). BBB A+ accredited. Note: Alfresco's manufacturer warranty (lifetime on certain components, 1-year full standard on most) may cover some failures; we produce written diagnostic reports for warranty submission when applicable."
  }
];

