---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<ServiceHero
  eyebrow="Alfresco AXE-30 · Built-In Luxury · 30-inch Stone Hearth · Gas-Fired · $120 Diagnostic"
  title="Alfresco AXE Pizza Oven Repair: Built-In Stone Hearth Service"
  subtitle="AXE-30 stone hearth replacement, refractory dome rebuild, gas valve, igniter. BBQG Inc. (Commerce, CA). Repair always justified through year 15. $120 dx across LA, OC, Ventura."
  heroImageTitle="Alfresco AXE Pizza Oven"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<!-- 01 INTRO + GRILL PAGE CROSS-LINK -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Alfresco AXE service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Built-in luxury 30-inch stone hearth. BBQG Inc. parent.</h2>

    <p>The Alfresco AXE-30 is the built-in luxury pizza oven we service most often in the Los Angeles area. 30-inch gas-fired stone hearth, $4,000 to $8,000 unit cost installed, made by BBQG Inc. in Commerce, California. Most-installed in Beverly Hills, Calabasas, Hidden Hills, Newport Coast, Pacific Palisades, and Brentwood outdoor kitchens, typically alongside an Alfresco grill suite.</p>

    <p>Important brand distinction: <strong>Alfresco's AXE pizza oven is a separate product family from their grill line.</strong> Same parent (BBQG Inc.), same authorized parts pipeline, but the AXE has its own catalog, its own service intervals, and its own failure modes. We have a separate page for the grill product line: <a href="/outdoor/brands/alfresco/">Alfresco grill service</a>. If your service ticket includes both grill and pizza oven (which it often does on full outdoor kitchen suites), one $120 dispatch covers both component diagnostics on the same visit.</p>

    <p>The repair-vs-replace conversation on AXE units is always tilted toward repair. Built-in luxury tier with 12 to 18 year service life means even a $1,200 repair at year 14 makes economic sense relative to $4,000+ unit cost plus cabinet refit. We see AXE units from 2015 still running strong with proper maintenance.</p>

    <p><strong>$120 outdoor commercial-tier diagnostic, waived with repair.</strong> BHGS #A49573 and EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410). 90-day SDAR labor warranty. Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura. Parent: <a href="/outdoor/pizza-oven-repair/">outdoor pizza oven repair pillar</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 BUILT-IN LUXURY MATH -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Built-in luxury repair math</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Repair always justified through year 15.</h2>

    <p>The economic case for repairing AXE units across their service life:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Unit cost.</strong> $4,000 to $8,000 for the AXE-30 alone, depending on configuration (gas type, accessory packages, model year). Installation in a custom cabinet adds another $2,000 to $5,000 in masonry, gas line, electrical, and finish work. Total replacement cost: $6,000 to $13,000.</li>
      <li><strong>Repair cost typical.</strong> $260 to $1,200 for major component refreshes (gas valve, igniter, hearth, refractory rebuild). Year 14 multi-component refresh: $780 to $1,200.</li>
      <li><strong>Service life extension.</strong> Major repair at year 12 to 14 typically extends usable life 5 to 7 years. Year 14 repair → year 19 to 21 functional unit.</li>
      <li><strong>Cabinet integration.</strong> Replacing the AXE means tearing into the surrounding cabinet trim, re-routing gas line, potentially re-finishing stone or stucco. The cabinet refit cost often exceeds the unit cost itself.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Math: $1,200 repair vs $6,000 to $13,000 replacement is a clear repair decision until the unit reaches end-of-engineering-life around year 18 to 20. We see AXE units from the 2015-2018 era still operating well in BH and Calabasas backyards.</p>

    <p>This is the opposite of the <a href="/outdoor/pizza-oven-repair/brands/ooni/">Ooni replace-tier conversation</a>. Different tier, different math. We tell you straight which side of the line your unit sits on at the $120 dx.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 COMMON FAILURES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Common AXE failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">In honest frequency order.</h2>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>1. Gas valve assembly drift (year 8-12)</h3>
      <p>Most common AXE service call. Manifold pressure regulator and burner valve drift over years; manometer test at the burner inlet confirms. Symptom: oven won't reach 700°F+, slow heat-up, won't hold target temperature during sustained use. $260 to $440 replacement, in-line labor.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>2. Stone hearth cracking (year 7-12)</h3>
      <p>Stone absorbs and radiates heat as part of cooking. Years of thermal cycling produce hairline surface cracks (cosmetic, no replacement needed) and eventually through-cracks (structural, replacement needed). Replacement hearth $260 to $560 depending on configuration. We rotate or replace based on actual structural condition assessment, not cosmetic appearance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>3. Refractory ceiling insulation rebuild (year 8-12)</h3>
      <p>Refractory cement in the dome ceiling cracks from years of thermal cycling. Symptom often paired with gas valve drift: oven won't reach 700°F+. Insulation rebuild $440 to $780 labor plus refractory materials ($120 to $260). Total $560 to $1,040.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>4. Spark electrode / ignition module (year 5-8)</h3>
      <p>Premium ignition system but components still wear with thermal cycling. Spark electrode replacement $200 to $340. Ignition module replacement $260 to $440.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>5. Door hinge and gasket (year 8-12)</h3>
      <p>Heavy stainless door with insulated core. Hinge spring tension fades over years; door gasket compresses. Hinge replacement $220 to $380. Gasket $180 to $280.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 LA OUTDOOR KITCHEN MARKET -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · LA outdoor kitchen market</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">BH, Calabasas, Hidden Hills, Newport, PP.</h2>

    <p>The Alfresco AXE-30 is the most-installed built-in luxury pizza oven in our service area. Geographic concentration:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Beverly Hills, Bel Air, Holmby Hills.</strong> Most density in our LA core territory. Typically paired with Alfresco grill suite or Lynx/Twin Eagles grill. Serviced from West Hollywood and Beverly Hills branches.</li>
      <li><strong>Calabasas, Hidden Hills, Westlake Village.</strong> Strong installation base in the Ventura County / west LA County borderlands. Serviced from Thousand Oaks branch.</li>
      <li><strong>Pacific Palisades, Brentwood, Bel Air West.</strong> Coastal-influenced installations; salt-air shorter component life by 1 to 2 years on gas valve assembly. Serviced from West Hollywood.</li>
      <li><strong>Newport Coast, Newport Beach, Crystal Cove.</strong> OC luxury concentration. Most coastal exposure, fastest gas valve and ignition wear. Serviced from Irvine branch.</li>
      <li><strong>Pasadena, San Marino, La Cañada.</strong> Inland luxury; longer service life on all components.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Annual or biannual maintenance contracts work well on full outdoor kitchen suites with AXE plus grill plus outdoor refrigeration. One $120 dispatch covers component diagnostic across the suite plus preventive cleaning. Catches refractory cracks at year 8 before they cost a full rebuild at year 12.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 PRICING -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">AXE repair costs.</h2>

    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Cost</th></tr>
      </thead>
